body:
The following example code works in modelsim, but doesnt in iverilog. 

It fails with ``error: A reference to a wire or reg (`s') is not allowed in a constant expression.``
The issue is `` select[s] [m]``. I can work around this by doing the slices manually, but the whole purpose of the array was to improve code readability.

```systemverilog

logic [S_COUNT:0] [M_COUNT:0] select;
logic [S_COUNT-1:0] [DATA_WIDTH-1:0] s_axis_tdata;
logic [M_COUNT-1:0] [DATA_WIDTH-1:0] m_axis_tdata;

always_comb begin
        for (int m = 0; m < M_COUNT; m = m+1) begin
            m_axis_tdata[m] = 0;
            for (int s = 0; s < S_COUNT; s = s+1) begin
                m_axis_tdata[m] |= s_axis_tdata[s] && select[s] [m];
            end
        end
    end
```

